Dear Professor Sanders,
After great deliberation and work with a wide array of other students in the class as well as utilizing as many resources as I could I have submitted a version of the final project. Though the final project is submitted I do not feel as though it is truly representative of the scope of this course as it relied on techniques and knowledge that could only be gained by use of external resources and course materials. Especially in the case of creating a dynamically updating webpage which without the benefit of taking hci concurrently with this course would require a great amount of extra work to understand and implement. As well as that after a period of time I found it more beneficial to re write the code base from scratch in order to implement the project in a way that made more since to me. Either way I hope that I have met the expected standards for the creation of this project in my submission and I wish you all the best. 
-Ethan Valencia
